{"parse":{"title":"balls","pageid":226226,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|Balls}}\n==English==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/bɔːlz/}}\n* {{audio|en|En-uk-balls.ogg|a=UK}}\n* {{IPA|en|/baːlz/|a=Northumbrian}}\n* {{IPA|en|/bɑlz/|a=cot-caught}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-balls.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Wodencafe-balls.wav|a=US,Texas}}\n* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Grendelkhan-balls.wav|a=US,Connecticut}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɔːlz|s=1}}\n\n{{rfc|en|overlaps with [[ball]], esp. the senses \"(mildly vulgar, slang, usually in the plural) A testicle.\", \"(in the plural) Nonsense.\", \"(in the plural) Courage.\"}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|en|noun form}}\n\n# {{plural of|en|ball}}\n#: {{ux|en|Can you believe he can juggle six '''balls''' at once?}}\n#* {{rfdate|en}} {{w|W. S. Gilbert}}, ''{{w|HMS Pinafore}}''\n#*: When the '''balls''' whistle free o'er the bright blue sea / We stand to our guns all day.\n# {{lb|en|vulgar|colloquial}} The [[testicles]].\n#: {{ux|en|After that shot, his '''balls''' were really hurting!}}\n#: {{ux|en|*groans* My '''b'''… '''b'''… '''ba'''… '''balls'''… '''balls'''…}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|p}}\n\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|vulgar|colloquial}} [[masculinity|Masculinity]], [[particularly]] [[strength]], [[courage]], and [[force of will]]; [[chutzpah]]; [[brazenness]].\n#* '''2007 September 28''', Graham Linehan, ''{{w|The IT Crowd}}'', Season 2, Episode 6:\n#*: ''Douglas:'' You've got [[spunk]]. And '''balls'''. And I like that in a woman.\n#: {{syn|en|Thesaurus:courage}}\n#: {{ux|en|He must have a lot of '''balls''' to talk to his boss that way.}}\n#: {{ux|en|He's the guy with the big '''balls''' in that group.}}\n#: {{ux|en|'''Balls''' is all that it takes to succeed.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Where the Air is Clear| page=80| url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1564783448| author=Carlos Fuentes; Sam Hileman| year=1960| passage='''Balls''' is all it takes to handle these people}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Havana Blue|page=137| url=https://books.google.com/books?isbn=1904738222| author=Leonardo Padura| year=2006| passage=“'''Balls''', gentlemen, '''balls''' is what you need to win at this game\"}}\n# {{lb|en|uncountable|UK|Ireland|Commonwealth|Hawaii|vulgar|colloquial }} {{synonym of|en|bollocks}}, {{ng|nonsense}}.\n#: {{ux|en|That's a load of '''balls'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|UK|Ireland|Commonwealth|Hawaii|vulgar}} A [[balls-up]]; a [[botch]]ed job.\n#: {{ux|en|Don't make a '''balls''' of it!}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|amazeballs|drag one's balls across|barse|blue balls|Colemanballs|dogballs|nutballs|ballsy|bust one's balls|bust someone's balls|[[cramp balls]] ({{taxlink|Daldinia concentrica|species}})|have someone by the balls|grab life by the balls|Billy Big Balls}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-see|follow the translations in the entry \"ball\"|ball}}\n\n{{trans-top|slang for testicles}}\n* Albanian: {{t+|sq|koqe|f-p}}\n* Armenian: {{t|hy|ձվեր|p}}, {{t+|hy|պլոր}}\n* Aromanian: {{t|rup|coalji|n-p}}, {{t|rup|boashi|f-p}}\n* Asturian: {{t+|ast|güevos|m-p}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{t|az|daşşaq}}\n* Bengali: {{t+|bn|বীচি}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|топки|f-p}}, {{t|bg|ташаци|m-p}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|collons|m-p}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Cantonese: {{t|yue|波子|tr=bo1 zi2}}, {{qualifier|vulgar}} {{t|yue|春子|tr=ceon1 zi2}}, {{t|yue|波珠|tr=bo1 zyu1}}\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|蛋蛋|tr=dàndàn}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|koule|f-p}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|nosser|c-p}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|ballen|m}}, {{t+|nl|kloten|m}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|kojono|alt=kojonoj}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|munad|p}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|pallit|p}}, {{t+|fi|munat|p}}, {{t+|fi|kassit|p}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|couilles|f-p}}, {{t+|fr|burnes|f-p}}, {{t+|fr|roustons|m-p}}, {{t+|fr|balloches|f-p}}, {{t+|fr|valseuses|f-p}}\n* Galician: {{t|gl|collóns|m-p}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|ყვერები}}, {{t|ka|კვაჯები}}, {{t|ka|ყოყორები}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Eier|p}}, {{t+|de|Klöten|p|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|αρχίδια|n-p}}\n* Hebrew: {{t|he|ביצים|p|tr=betzim}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|tök}}\n* Indonesian: {{t|id|peler}} {{qualifier|vulgar}}, {{t|id|biji salak}}, {{t|id|biji peler}} {{qualifier|vulgar}}\n* Interlingua: {{t|ia|coleones}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|balle|f-p}}, {{t+|it|palle|f-p}}, {{t+|it|coglioni|m-p}}, {{t+|it|testicoli|m-p}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|金玉|tr=kintama}}\n* Javanese: {{t+|jv|konthol}} {{qualifier|vulgar}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|cōleī|m-p}} {{qualifier|vulgar}}\n* Lithuanian: {{t|lt|kiaušai|m-p}}\n* Persian: {{t+|fa|خایه|tr=xâye}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|jaja|p}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|saco|m}}, {{t+|pt|bolas|f-p}}, {{t+|pt|colhões|m-p}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|boașe|n-p}}, {{t+|ro|coaie|n-p}}, {{t+|ro|ouă|n-p}}\n* Russian: {{t|ru|муде́}}, {{t+|ru|яйцо|alt=я́йца|n-p}}\n* Serbo-Croatian: {{t+|sh|jaja|n-p}}, {{t+|sh|muda|n-p}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|gule|f-p}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|jajca|n-p}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|huevos|m-p}}, {{t+|es|pelotas|f-p}}, {{t+|es|cojones|m-p}}, {{t+|es|bolas|f-p}}\n* Tagalog: {{t+|tl|betlog}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|taşak}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|איי|n-p|alt=אייער}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-top|slang for masculinity, inclusive of strength, courage, and force of will}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|дупе|n}} {{qualifier|сленг}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|ous|m-p}}, {{t+|ca|collons|m-p}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|有種|tr=yǒuzhǒng}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|ballen}}, {{t+|nl|kloten}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|muna}} {{qualifier|in the idiom \"[[olla]] [[munaa]]\"}}, {{t+|fi|kantti}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|couilles|f-p}}\n* Galician: {{t|gl|collóns|m-p}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|ტრაკი}}, {{t|ka|ტრაკის ქონა}}\n* German: {{qualifier|vulgar}} {{t|de|Arsch in der Hose}}, {{t+|de|Mut|m}}, {{qualifier|colloquial}} {{t+|de|Mumm|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|αρχίδια|n-p}}\n* Hebrew: {{t|he|ביצים|m-p|tr=betzim}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|tökös}}\n* Interlingua: {{t|ia|coleones}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|palle|f-p}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|jaja|p}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|colhões|m-p}}\n* Romanian: {{t|ro|pulă în pantaloni|n-p}}, {{t|ro|sânge în coaie|n-p}}, {{t|ro|cur în pantaloni|n-p}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|huevos|m-p}}, {{t+|es|cojones|m-p}}\n* Swedish: {{t+|sv|stake|c}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|vulgar|transitive}} Speaking or acting with [[bravado]] to achieve (something)\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=A Killing Trade|author=Tiny Boyles; Hank Nuwer; William Boyles|year=1981|page=191|ISBN=0872169022|passage=You're going up to the front door of that mansion and '''ballsing''' your way inside.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=The Accord|author=Keith Brooke|year=2009|page=135|passage=The poor fuck is broken-hearted, and he thinks he is '''ballsing''' it out really well, but he isn't.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=Make You: Stake You #2|author=Claire Farrell|year=2014|passage=He was '''ballsing''' his way through the conversation. For the first time, I caught a glimpse of something vulnerable behind the usual brashness.}}\n# {{lb|en|vulgar|slang}} To engage in [[sexual intercourse]].\n\n===Verb===\n{{head|en|verb form}}\n\n# {{infl of|en|ball||s-verb-form}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n* {{l|en|balls about}}, {{l|en|balls around}}\n* {{l|en|balls on}}\n* {{l|en|balls up}}\n\n===Adverb===\n{{en-adv|-}}\n\n# {{lb|en|slang}} [[very|Very]]. {{non-gloss|Intensifier.}}\n#: {{ux|en|It is '''balls''' cold out there.}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|intensifier: very}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|vitun}}, {{t+|fi|helvetin}}, {{t|fi|helkkarin}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|putain de}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|tök}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Further reading===\n* {{pedia|ball}}\n* {{pedia|testicle}}\n* {{pedia|courage}}\n\n{{C|en|Genitalia}}\n\n==Catalan==\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{ca-IPA}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{head|ca|noun form}}\n\n# {{plural of|ca|ball}}"}}